# Brace style

Omit curly braces when a control-flow body is a single statement. Put short single-statement bodies on the **same line** as the condition when they fit.

```typescript
// Good — one line
if (!token) return false;
if (!process.env.OPENAI_API_KEY?.trim()) throw new Error('OPENAI_API_KEY is not set');
if (err.code === 'EBADCSRFTOKEN') return res.status(403).json({ error: 'Invalid CSRF token' });

// Bad — unnecessary braces
if (!token) {
  return false;
}

// Bad — single statement split onto the next line
if (!process.env.OPENAI_API_KEY?.trim())
  throw new Error('OPENAI_API_KEY is not set');
```

Keep braces when the body has multiple statements or spans multiple lines:

```typescript
if (!secret) {
  secret = tokens.secretSync();
  writeSecret(req, res, secret);
}
```

Applies to `if`, `else`, `for`, `while`, and `do`.
